2016年6月23日，[[英國|英國]]以[[英國去留歐盟公投|公投]]決定[[英國脫歐|脫離]][[歐洲聯盟|歐洲聯盟]]。2017年3月29日，{{tsl|en|United Kingdom invocation of Article 50 of the Treaty on European Union|英國引用歐盟條約第50條}}，通知歐盟脫離的決定。同年6月，雙方正式開展'''英國脫歐談判'''。根據第50條，脫歐談判為期兩年，除非雙方同意延長談判期。

==時間線==
{{main|英國脫歐談判}}

=== 2017年6月 ===
2017年6月19日，英國[[脫離歐盟事務大臣|脫離歐盟事務大臣]][[戴德偉|戴德偉]]抵達[[布魯塞爾|布魯塞爾]]，開始與歐盟首席談判代表[[米歇爾·巴尼耶|米歇爾·巴尼耶]]進行談判<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40321271 |title=Brexit negotiations: Barnier rules out 'concessions' |date=2017-06-19 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-06-23 |archive-date=2019-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728164327/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40321271 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。雙方同意職責範圍以及舉行五輪談判，而最後一輪將於10月第二個星期舉行。英國和歐盟將聚焦三項議題：歐盟公民居英權及其相反（居留權）、英國對歐盟的財政義務（{{tsl|en|Brexit divorce bill|英國脫歐費用|脫歐費}}又稱分手費）、北愛爾蘭與愛爾蘭共和國之間的邊界（兩愛邊境）<ref name=":2">{{cite web |url=https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/eu-uk-art-50-terms-reference_agreed_amends_en.pdf |title=Terms of Reference for the Article 50 TEU negotiations |date=2017-06-19 |website=[[歐盟委員會|歐盟委員會]] |access-date=2017-08-29 |archive-date=2017-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829213212/https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/eu-uk-art-50-terms-reference_agreed_amends_en.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8017 |title=Brexit: the talks begin |date=2017-07-12 |website=英國下議院圖書館 |accessdate=2017-08-20 |archive-date=2017-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820203409/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8017 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Let the Brussels games begin |url=https://www.economist.com/britain/2017/06/22/let-the-brussels-games-begin |accessdate=2018-09-22 |work=經濟學人 |archive-date=2018-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180923052143/https://www.economist.com/britain/2017/06/22/let-the-brussels-games-begin |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

22號，英國首相文翠珊在[[歐盟高峰會|歐洲理事會]]的會議上承諾，在英國合法居留的歐盟公民將不會被強制出境，又有條件地提出，任何歐盟公民只要在2017年3月至2019年3月期間某一日之前居英達五年的話，將可享有英國公民的權利，前提是歐方亦向居住在歐盟境內的英國僑民提供相同待遇。歐盟各國領袖未有即時回應此提案，[[欧洲理事会主席|歐洲理事會主席]][[當奴·圖斯克|當奴·圖斯克]]重申理事會非用作脫歐談判，而[[欧盟委员会主席|歐盟委員會主席]][[让-克洛德·容克|让-克洛德·容克]]亦強調不會在此談判<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/22/donald-tusk-john-lennon-eu-summit-uk-britain-brexit |newspaper=衛報 |location=倫敦 |title=Donald Tusk echoes John Lennon to suggest UK could stay in EU |first=Daniel |last=Boffey |date=2017-06-22 |accessdate=2017-06-23 |archive-date=2017-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170625115557/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jun/22/donald-tusk-john-lennon-eu-summit-uk-britain-brexit |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

四日後，英國首相向下議院闡述其居留權方案，但歐方仍然拒絕加快在月尾前就僑民達成協定<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lemonde.fr/europe/article/2017/06/27/brexit-les-expatries-premier-bras-de-fer-entre-londres-et-bruxelles_5151696_3214.html |newspaper=[[世界报_(法国)|世界報]] |location=巴黎 |language=fr |title=Brexit: les expatriés, premier bras de fer entre Londres et Bruxelles |trans-title=Brexit: Expatriates, the first arm-wrestling match between London and Brussels |first=Eric |last=Abert |date=2017-06-27 |accessdate=2017-06-27 |archive-date=2020-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113225741/http://www.lemonde.fr/europe/article/2017/06/27/brexit-les-expatries-premier-bras-de-fer-entre-londres-et-bruxelles_5151696_3214.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="auto4">{{cite news |last=Bush |first=Stephen |date=2017-05-02 |title=Theresa May and Jean-Claude Juncker's dinner leaked because no-one thinks Brexit will work |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2017/05/theresa-may-and-jean-claude-junckers-dinner-leaked-because-no-one-thinks |newspaper=[[新政治家|新政治家]] |access-date=2017-05-15 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127221536/https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2017/05/theresa-may-and-jean-claude-junckers-dinner-leaked-because-no-one-thinks |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而他們亦希望[[歐洲法院|歐洲法院]]在英國脫歐後繼續享有對英國境內歐盟公民的司法權<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nzz.ch/international/brexit-verhandlungen-london-will-eu-buerger-in-grossbritannien-halten-ld.1302924 |title=Brexit-Verhandlungen: London will EU-Bürger in Grossbritannien halten |trans-title=Brexit negotiations: London wants to keep EU citizens in Britain |newspaper=[[新苏黎世报|新苏黎世报]] |language=de |date=2017-06-26 |accessdate=2017-06-27 |archive-date=2018-06-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615191718/https://www.nzz.ch/international/brexit-verhandlungen-london-will-eu-buerger-in-grossbritannien-halten-ld.1302924 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Reality Check: Britain and EU at odds over citizens' rights |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40413041 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |date=2017-06-27 |accessdate=2017-06-27 |archive-date=2019-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190623201500/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40413041 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 2017年7月 ===
第二輪談判於七月中在布魯塞爾開展，同場有98個英方談判代表和45個歐方代表，被視為實質談判的開始<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/uk/the-scotsman/20170718/281625305353947|title=EU hands Britain a two-month deadline on Brexit talks|last=Gourtsoyannis|first=Paris|date=2017-07-18|accessdate=2017-07-19|newspaper=[[苏格兰人报|苏格兰人报]]|archive-date=2019-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145752/https://www.pressreader.com/uk/the-scotsman/20170718/281625305353947|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="HoC-July">{{cite web|url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8068|title=Brexit: the July negotiations|date=2017-08-02|website=下議院圖書館|accessdate=2017-08-20|archive-date=2019-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145749/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8068|dead-url=no}}</ref>。雙方在兩愛邊境問題上有進展，但另外兩範疇都遇到阻滯：英方促請歐盟詳列預料高達650億歐羅的脫歐費各個細項，而歐方則批評英方提出的居留權方案<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/eu-and-uk-singing-off-same-hymn-sheet-on-northern-ireland-1.3160534|title=EU and UK 'singing off same hymn sheet' on Northern Ireland|date=2017-07-20|newspaper=[[愛爾蘭時報|愛爾蘭時報]]|accessdate=2017-07-20|archive-date=2019-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411152811/https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/eu-and-uk-singing-off-same-hymn-sheet-on-northern-ireland-1.3160534|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在總結談判成果的記者會上，戴氏未有承諾英國會向歐盟付脫歐款項；而巴尼耶亦表明不會就歐洲法院司法權妥協<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nzz.ch/international/zweite-verhandlungsrunde-in-bruessel-london-bleibt-zu-brexit-rechnung-unverbindlich-ld.1307012|title=Zweite Verhandlungsrunde in Brüssel: London bleibt zu Brexit-Rechnung unverbindlich|last=Nuspliger|first=Niklus|date=2017-07-20|newspaper=[[新蘇黎世報|新蘇黎世報]]|accessdate=2017-07-21|language=de|trans-title=Second round of negotiations in Brussels: London remains non-committal to Brexit bill|archive-date=2019-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402102549/https://www.nzz.ch/international/zweite-verhandlungsrunde-in-bruessel-london-bleibt-zu-brexit-rechnung-unverbindlich-ld.1307012|dead-url=no}}</ref>，亦拒絕由英國和歐盟法官組成新司法機構的提案<ref>{{cite web|title=Brexit: UK and EU at odds over 'exit bill'|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40662740|date=2017-07-21|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]|access-date=2017-07-21|archive-date=2019-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728202639/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-40662740|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

雙方亦共同公佈文件，對比英國和歐盟在不同問題上的立場<ref name="jointcomparison">{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/joint-technical-note-on-the-comparison-of-eu-uk-positions-on-citizens-rights |title=Joint technical note on the comparison of EU-UK positions on citizens' rights |date=2017-07-20 |website=Department for Exiting the European Union |accessdate=2017-09-30 |archive-date=2020-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201115164604/https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/joint-technical-note-on-the-comparison-of-eu-uk-positions-on-citizens-rights |dead-url=no }}</ref>。雙方在愛爾蘭邊境問題上，強調會繼續遵守《[[貝爾法斯特協議|貝爾法斯特協議]]》<ref name="HoC-July" />；巴尼耶呼籲英國在八月的談判時澄清三個議題上的取態，包括英方如何維繫[[共同旅行區|共同旅行區]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_SPEECH-17-2108_en.htm |title=Speaking points by Michel Barnier at the press conference following the second round of Article 50 negotiations with the United Kingdom |date=2017-07-20 |website=European Commission |accessdate=2017-08-20 |archive-date=2019-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626224057/http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_SPEECH-17-2108_en.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 2017年8月 ===
8月16日，英國政府首次發表多份文件，講述英國脫歐後的願景，和貿易及海關安排<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.joc.com/international-logistics/brexit-customs-proposal-short-details-say-uk-forwarders_20170816.html |title=UK forwarders: Brexit customs proposal short on details |date=2017-08-16 |newspaper={{tsl|en|The Journal of Commerce||The Journal of Commerce}} |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145749/https://www.joc.com/international-logistics/brexit-customs-proposal-short-details-say-uk-forwarders_20170816.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。8月23日，文翠珊宣佈英國將會在2019年3月過後的脫歐過渡期結束後，脫離歐洲法院的直接司法管轄範圍，但英歐法庭將互相留意對方此後的判決<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41012265 |title=PM: UK leaving EU court's jurisdiction |date=2017-08-23 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526025751/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41012265 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。其中一份文件則呼籲，英歐市場上現已流通的貨物毋須另加限制<ref name="auto3">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41089257 |title=Brexit: Jean-Claude Juncker criticises UK's position papers |date=2017-08-30 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |access-date=2017-08-30 |archive-date=2019-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729013925/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41089257 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

第三輪脫歐談判於8月28日、同樣在布魯塞爾舉行。容克對英方所有文件不感滿意，重申只有解決分手費問題後，才會進行貿易談判。容克早前表示分手費可能達550億歐羅，而歐盟預算專員{{tsl|en|Günther Oettinger|管特·敖霆拿}}認為英方應分期付款至2023年<ref>{{cite news|title=Briten müssen bis 2023 Zahlungen an die EU leisten|trans-title=The British must make payments to the EU until 2023|newspaper=[[世界報_(德國)|世界報]]|url=https://www.welt.de/politik/ausland/article168235792/Briten-muessen-bis-2023-Zahlungen-an-die-EU-leisten.html|accessdate=2017-09-02|first=Christoph|last=Schiltz|date=2016-09-02|language=de|archive-date=2019-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322155136/https://www.welt.de/politik/ausland/article168235792/Briten-muessen-bis-2023-Zahlungen-an-die-EU-leisten.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但遭到英國政府大臣斥責費用貴得離譜<ref name="auto3"/>''。''《愛爾蘭時報》解釋了雙方分歧，英方理解{{tsl|en|Multiannual Financial Framework|多個年度財務框架}}的七年期為成員國所同意的2014年至2020年，歐洲議會的角色是規劃下一年度預算，而財務框架並非具法律約束力的成員國財政義務；英國政府認為財務框架就不同項目設下開支上限，再經年度財政預算程序大幅修訂，因此成員國真正的法律義務應依照修訂版本而定；不過歐盟委員會則認為應按照各成員國曾經同意過的份額，分配財務框架的金額，作為英國脫歐費用<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Irish Times |date=2017-08-31 |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/huge-gulf-in-negotiations-on-uk-s-brexit-bill-1.3203800 |accessdate=2017-09-02 |title=Huge gulf in negotiations on UK's Brexit bill |archive-date=2019-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402084351/https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/huge-gulf-in-negotiations-on-uk-s-brexit-bill-1.3203800 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

兩愛邊境問題則傳出有突破進展，英廷保證歐盟公民可以自由往返進出[[共同旅行區|共同旅行區]]（當中涵蓋英國和愛爾蘭）<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Irish Times |date=2017-09-01 |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/major-breakthrough-in-irish-strand-of-brexit-talks-1.3205341 |accessdate=2017-09-02 |title=Major breakthrough in Irish strand of Brexit talks |archive-date=2019-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190305174948/https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/europe/major-breakthrough-in-irish-strand-of-brexit-talks-1.3205341 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。英國廣播公司的歐洲特派記者認為「英國對磋商的態度比歐盟更為樂觀」<ref name="auto3" />。同樣傳出好消息並達成協定的還有多個議題：保障外勞（即工作地與居住地非同一國家）權益、英國承認脫歐前後的社會安全貢獻、延續居英歐僑和居歐英僑的醫保補償<ref>{{cite web |url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8082 |title=Brexit: the August negotiations |date=2017-09-06 |website=House of Commons Library |accessdate=2017-09-09 |archive-date=2019-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145752/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8082 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。雙方立場的共同文件亦作出更新<ref name="jointcomparison" />。

在本輪談判閉幕記者會上，巴尼耶特別點名提及英歐兩大分歧：歐洲法院保障公民權利的角色，以及英國應付的財政義務。他指出「時日如飛」，「以現今速度而言，我們將難以達成理想進展，而向歐洲理事會建議就未來關係展開討論」<ref>{{cite web |url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_SPEECH-17-3043_en.htm |title=Speech by Michel Barnier at the press conference following the third round of Article 50 negotiations with the United Kingdom |date=2017-08-31 |website=European Commission |access-date=2017-09-06 |archive-date=2019-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190626224059/http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_SPEECH-17-3043_en.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 2017年9月 ===
[[File:VillaDEste.jpg|thumb]]湖邊的[[埃斯特别墅_(切尔诺比奥)|埃斯特别墅]]舉行]]

9月2日，歐洲的精英雲集{{tsl|en|Ambrosetti Forum|岩布西提論壇}}。巴尼耶在論壇解釋他的談判目標：「教懂英國人和其他人何謂脫離歐盟」<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/michel-barnier-david-davis-brexit-educational-teach-uk-leaving-single-market-negotiations-a7927336.html |title=EU chief negotiator Michel Barnier says he will 'teach the UK what leaving the single market means' |newspaper=The Independent |date=2017-09-03 |access-date=2017-09-03 |archive-date=2020-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207234346/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/michel-barnier-david-davis-brexit-educational-teach-uk-leaving-single-market-negotiations-a7927336.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此番言論隨即引起英國國內不滿，但英國廣播公司的記者則認為是含沙射影，意在法國和荷蘭的疑歐派、波蘭和匈牙利的疑歐派政府、以及將會舉行的德國、奧地利和意大利的選舉<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-41141650 |title=Brexit: A lakeside view of Barnier's tough talk |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |date=2017-09-04 |access-date=2017-09-04 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127005155/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-41141650 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

9月5日，戴德偉在下議院回顧夏季談判時表示，雙方在歐盟英僑的醫保服務和兩愛邊境未來兩個議題上有「實質進展」，惟分手費則尚未能收窄分歧<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41155578 |title=Brexit: 'Significant differences' over exit bill says Davis |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |date=2017-09-05 |access-date=2017-09-05 |archive-date=2019-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729021740/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41155578 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。戴氏估計「財政爭拗將持續至談判結束，猶如歐洲人一貫的『一同意就要同意全部』風格」<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Irish Times |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/uk/britain-may-hold-out-on-brexit-divorce-cash-until-last-minute-1.3210638 |title=Britain may hold out on Brexit divorce cash until last minute |date=2017-09-05 |accessdate=2017-09-05 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112015004/https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/uk/britain-may-hold-out-on-brexit-divorce-cash-until-last-minute-1.3210638 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。文翠珊翌日表示，脫歐後的英國政府將會向居英的歐盟公民實施新的移民管制<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/06/theresa-may-backs-new-eu-immigration-controls-after-brexit-leak |title=Theresa May defends new EU immigration controls after Brexit leak |first1=Heather |last1=Stewart |first2=Peter |last2=Walker |date=2017-09-06 |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112021243/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/06/theresa-may-backs-new-eu-immigration-controls-after-brexit-leak |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

9月7日，歐盟專責小組公佈兩愛邊境問題對話的指導原則，除了強調四月公布的原則之外，亦強調維護貝爾法斯特協議和共同旅行區的重要性<ref>{{cite web|url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-17-3105_en.htm|title=Brexit: European Commission publishes guiding principles on Ireland and Northern Ireland|date=2017-09-07|website=European Commission|access-date=2017-12-15|archive-date=2019-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190921140753/https://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-17-3105_en.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。9月9日，歐盟委員會亦發表數份談判文件，包括「愛爾蘭／北愛爾蘭議題對話指導原則」。歐盟在原則文件中承認，脫歐後的兩愛邊境問題應由英方提出方案，亦強調兩愛的特別方案不應被視為脫歐後英歐就邊境和海關管制事宜的範本，包括[[欧洲联盟签证政策|歐洲旅行資訊及授權系統]]<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Irish Times |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/don-t-use-irish-border-as-test-case-for-eu-uk-border-says-barnier-1.3212836 |title=Don't use Irish Border as test case for EU-UK border, says Barnier |date=2017-09-07 |accessdate=2017-09-07 |archive-date=2020-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200508064921/https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/do-not-use-irish-border-as-test-case-for-eu-uk-border-says-barnier-1.3212836 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

21號，文翠珊會同內閣<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-20/may-s-said-to-mull-brexit-bill-offer-to-unlock-talks-in-florence |title=May Clinches Cabinet Support Ahead of Florence Brexit Speech |date=2017-09-20 |website=Bloomberg |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111232241/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-20/may-s-said-to-mull-brexit-bill-offer-to-unlock-talks-in-florence |dead-url=no }}</ref>，同意在大約兩年的實施期（亦稱過渡期）期間履行承諾，向歐盟財政預算注資200億歐羅，讓歐盟其他國家毋須額外付款或取得較少資金<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/9b183886-9faf-11e7-8cd4-932067fbf946|title=Five key points from Theresa May's speech|last1=Wright|first1=Robert|date=2017-09-22|newspaper=Financial Times|accessdate=2017-09-26|archive-date=2018-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830142312/https://www.ft.com/content/9b183886-9faf-11e7-8cd4-932067fbf946|dead-url=no}}{{subscription}}</ref><ref name="bbc.com">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41342580 |title=May 'to offer 20bn euros' transitional deal |date=2017-09-21 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2021-01-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116140255/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41342580 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。22號，文翠珊在意大利[[佛羅倫斯|佛羅倫斯]]公佈脫歐大計<ref name="youtubesep21">{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lUFpahcEOX8 |title=Theresa May's Brexit speech in Florence – watch live Guardian News |date=2017-09-22 |via=YouTube |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2017-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922144629/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lUFpahcEOX8 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="sep21" />，除了注資財政預算和繼續接受歐盟移民外<ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/09/21/europe/uk-may-brexit-speech-florence/index.html |title=UK PM seeks to break Brexit deadlock |first=Laura |last=Smith-Spark |date=2017-09-22 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2017-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922025432/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/09/21/europe/uk-may-brexit-speech-florence/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，亦提出英國與歐盟之間「大膽嶄新的安全關係」，而且將會是「前所未見的深入」，讓兩國繼續在科研和安全等對雙方都有利的議題上繼續合作<ref name="sep21">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41355642 |title=Keep EU trade as it is until 2021 – May |date=2017-09-22 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2017-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922161141/http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41355642 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="youtubesep21" />。文太亦確定英國不會阻撓容克提出歐盟進一步一體化的建議<ref name="sep21" /><ref name="youtubesep21" />。巴尼耶歡迎英方的「建設性」提案<ref name="brexitoct18" />，但重申要放在談判桌上才可達致有意義的進展<ref name="brexitoct18" />。[[法國總統|法國總統]][[伊曼努爾·馬克龍|伊曼努爾·馬克龍]]堅持，除非英國澄清「如何規管歐盟公民、脫歐的財政問題、以及愛爾蘭問題」，否則歐盟不會就英歐未來關係開展談<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41369600 |title=Brexit: UK needs to clarify issues – Macron |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |date=2017-09-23 |access-date=2017-09-23 |archive-date=2019-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729080425/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41369600 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但他亦承認文翠珊的演講已就其中兩點起了個頭<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/brexit-cannot-continue-three-main-points-emmanuel-macron-theresa-may-florence-speech-a7962426.html |title=Macron says UK needs to clarify its position on three main Brexit issues before resuming talks |date=2017-09-22 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112012416/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/brexit-cannot-continue-three-main-points-emmanuel-macron-theresa-may-florence-speech-a7962426.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[愛爾蘭總理|愛爾蘭總理]][[李歐·瓦拉德卡|李歐·瓦拉德卡]]「謹慎歡迎」文翠珊的計劃，認為她提及了共同旅行區和北愛和平進程，以及談判雙方都不希望兩愛邊境有構築物，都是一個好開始，但之後仍要在談判桌上作更多解說<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2017/0922/906831-politics-varadkar/ |title=Taoiseach gives 'cautious welcome' to May's speech |date=2017-09-22 |publisher={{tsl|en|RTÉ News||RTÉ News}} |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021113821/https://www.rte.ie/news/politics/2017/0922/906831-politics-varadkar/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。歐洲議會談判代表[[居伊·伏思達|居伊·伏思達]]回應時指「歐盟公民登記在英國居住或工作的全新機制完全不可行」<ref>{{cite news |first=Caroline |last=Mortimer |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-latest-theresa-may-eu-migrant-registration-shot-down-immigration-a7962256.html |title=Brexit: Theresa May's plan for EU migrant registry shot down by Guy Verhofstadt |newspaper=The Independent |publisher=Independent Print Limited |date=2017-09-23 |accessdate=2017-09-25 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111232344/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-latest-theresa-may-eu-migrant-registration-shot-down-immigration-a7962256.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

歐盟代表強調雙方需要在2018年10月前達成協議，讓英歐的議會分別批准協議<ref name=brexitoct18>{{cite news |url=http://www.daytondailynews.com/business/the-latest-brexit-chief-welcomes-constructive-speech/eKv8542YSNWjBQCDclPX2M/ |title=The Latest: EU's Brexit chief welcomes 'constructive' speech |date=2017-09-22 |newspaper={{tsl|en|Dayton Daily News||Dayton Daily News}} |access-date=2018-08-30 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923002029/http://www.daytondailynews.com/business/the-latest-brexit-chief-welcomes-constructive-speech/eKv8542YSNWjBQCDclPX2M/ |archive-date=2017-09-23 }}</ref>。[[工党_(英国)|英國工黨]]議員兼{{tsl|en|Shadow Home Secretary|影子內政大臣}}[[黛安娜·艾勃特|艾德雅]]宣佈她本人將會支持文翠珊的脫歐時間表方案<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.sky.com/story/diane-abbott-backs-theresa-mays-two-year-brexit-transition-plan-11051125 |title=Diane Abbott backs Theresa May's two-year Brexit transition plan |date=2017-09-24 |publisher=Sky News |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123170257/https://news.sky.com/story/diane-abbott-backs-theresa-mays-two-year-brexit-transition-plan-11051125 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

因應文翠珊的演說，第四輪談判延遲一星期至9月25號展開<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-12/u-k-eu-are-said-to-delay-next-round-of-brexit-negotiations|title=U.K. and EU Delay Next Round of Brexit Negotiations|date=2017-09-12|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|access-date=2017-09-26|archive-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729164849/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-12/u-k-eu-are-said-to-delay-next-round-of-brexit-negotiations|dead-url=no}}</ref>。巴尼耶表示他未獲歐盟成員國授權討論文翠珊提出的過渡期方案，而戴德偉重申英國只會在英歐得以實現「特別夥伴關係」的情況下才會履行對歐盟的承諾<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu/hopes-and-frustrations-as-brexit-talks-resume-after-may-speech-idUSKCN1BZ124|title=Hopes and frustrations as Brexit talks resume after May speech|date=2017-09-24|access-date=2017-09-28|agency=Reuters|archive-date=2019-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508100432/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu/hopes-and-frustrations-as-brexit-talks-resume-after-may-speech-idUSKCN1BZ124|dead-url=no}}</ref>。是次談判包括三個談判小組（分別牽涉公民權利、財政問題和其他事宜）與主管的會面，而兩愛問題則交由統籌團隊負責；雙方亦開始討論執行脫歐協議的技術層面<ref name="European Union 2017">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/programme-for-fourth-round-of-uk-eu-article-50-negotiations|title=Programme for fourth round of UK-EU Article 50 negotiations|date=2017-09-25|website=Department for Exiting the European Union|access-date=2018-08-30|archive-date=2019-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217081727/https://www.gov.uk/government/news/programme-for-fourth-round-of-uk-eu-article-50-negotiations|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

戴氏複述文太的限時過渡期要求，而英國亦提出將脫歐協議納入英國法律彙編，確保英國法院能夠引用協議作判決。不過就歐洲法院的角色和未來判例法的法律地位則仍未有共識<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/politics/859890/Brexit-news-EU-David-Davis-Michel-Barnier-progress-talks|title=Brexit breakthrough? How FOUR key battlegrounds from the fourth round of talks unfolded|last=Gutteridge|first=Nick|date=2017-09-28|newspaper=Daily Express|access-date=2017-10-01|archive-date=2019-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007071549/https://www.express.co.uk/news/politics/859890/Brexit-news-EU-David-Davis-Michel-Barnier-progress-talks|dead-url=no}}</ref>。巴尼耶歡迎英國繼續貢獻給歐盟預算，但對2020年後英方的義務有保留；戴氏強調英方尚未落實注資額<ref name=":1" />。至於兩愛問題上，討論具建設性但欠缺實際進展<ref>{{cite web|url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8104|title=Brexit: the September negotiations|date=2017-10-06|website=House of Commons Library|accessdate=2017-10-14|archive-date=2019-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810175702/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8104|dead-url=no}}</ref>。英國接受歐盟對「限期前合法居住的公民」的定義，惟限期日尚未達成共識；雙方亦同意永久和臨時居住地的定義。英國就返回權提出的定義為離國連續兩年或以上，比起現行歐盟法律更為長；不過雙方仍然就家屬權利僵持不下<ref name="jointcomparison" />。

=== 2017年10月 ===
10月9日，文翠珊在國會表示，一旦未能與歐盟達成貿易協議的話，英國可以成為「獨立貿易國」<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41546701|title=UK explores 'no deal' Brexit|date=2017-10-09|publisher=BBC|access-date=2017-11-01|archive-date=2019-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728174218/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41546701|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

最後一輪的第五輪談判在10月9、10、12號舉行<ref name=":2" />，雙方沒有計劃舉行更多談判<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-talks-negotiations-deadlock-article-50-theresa-may-eu-david-davis-a7999156.html|title=No further Brexit talks yet scheduled as negotiations hit deadlock|last=Stone|first=Jon|date=2017-10-14|newspaper=The Independent|access-date=2017-10-15|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112042626/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-talks-negotiations-deadlock-article-50-theresa-may-eu-david-davis-a7999156.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The U.K. Is Stalling on New Brexit Talks|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-10-27/u-k-stalling-on-new-brexit-talks-as-clock-ticks-down-to-summit|date=2017-10-27|last1=Ross|first1=Tim|last2=Wishart|first2=Ian|website=Bloomberg|access-date=2017-10-30|archive-date=2019-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145750/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-10-27/u-k-stalling-on-new-brexit-talks-as-clock-ticks-down-to-summit|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在公民權議題上，雙方就家屬團聚和適用於歐盟公民的英國社會保障福利分歧仍大，但亦達成技術性進展，英方有意提供一更為簡便的登記程序<ref>{{cite web |url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8125 |title=Brexit: the October negotiations |date=2017-10-27 |website=House of Commons Library |access-date=2017-10-30 |archive-date=2019-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030230312/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-8125 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=":0" />。兩愛問題上，雙方繼續就脫歐後合作以及未來挑戰制定框架<ref name=":0">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41585430 |title=Deadlock over UK's Brexit bill – Barnier |date=2017-10-12 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |access-date=2017-10-14 |archive-date=2020-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204120215/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41585430 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。財政方面則爭持不下，巴尼耶歡迎文翠珊的佛羅倫斯演說，但因英國仍未詳列付款細項的意願，而未有在談判中談及<ref>{{cite web|url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_STATEMENT-17-3921_en.htm|title=Press statement by Michel Barnier following the fifth round of Article 50 negotiations with the United Kingdom|date=2017-10-12|website=European Commission|access-date=2017-10-14|archive-date=2019-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190815003501/https://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_STATEMENT-17-3921_en.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

16號，文太與容克在布魯塞爾共進晚餐，雙方形容氣氛「積極和友善」，爾後發表的聯合聲明同意應在未來數月加速談判<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41642051 |title=PM and EU: Let's speed up Brexit talks |date=2017-10-17 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190323081105/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41642051 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/theresa-may-and-eu-president-jeanclaude-juncker-promise-to-speed-up-brexit-talks-after-constructive-a3660231.html |title=Theresa May and Jean-Claude Juncker promise to 'accelerate' Brexit talks after 'constructive and friendly dinner' |date=2017-10-16 |newspaper={{tsl|en|London Evening Standard||London Evening Standard}} |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145749/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/theresa-may-and-eu-president-jeanclaude-juncker-promise-to-speed-up-brexit-talks-after-constructive-a3660231.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-talks-theresa-may-jean-claude-juncker-brussels-dinner-accelerate-a8003866.html |title=Theresa May and EU president Juncker agree Brexit talks should 'accelerate' |date=2017-10-16 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112011002/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-talks-theresa-may-jean-claude-juncker-brussels-dinner-accelerate-a8003866.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/16/theresa-may-jean-claude-juncker-pledge-accelerate-brexit-negotiations/ |title=Theresa May and Jean-Claude Juncker pledge to 'accelerate' Brexit talks – but fail to break deadlock |first1=Steven |last1=Swinford |first2=James |last2=Crisp |first3=Peter |last3=Foster |date=2017-10-16 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804105628/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/16/theresa-may-jean-claude-juncker-pledge-accelerate-brexit-negotiations/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不過，德國的《[[法兰克福汇报|星期日法蘭克福匯報]]》在報導中大致描繪是次會議為負面。該報章亦曾以此形容同年較早前的一場晚宴，當時赴宴者有文翠珊、{{tsl|en|Olly Robbins|傲利·樂彬}}、戴德偉、容克和巴尼耶。容克幕僚長{{tsl|en|Martin Selmayr|馬田·西迷}}被指再次放風爆料，試圖破壞談判，但他否認指控；德國總理默克爾亦據報否認牽涉其中<ref>{{cite news |title=Merkel "wütend" über Bericht zu May und Juncker |language=de |trans-title=Merkel "angry" about report on May and Juncker |url=https://derstandard.at/2000066611637/Merkel-wuetend-ueber-Bericht-zu-May-und-Juncker |date=2017-10-24 |accessdate=2017-10-25 |newspaper={{tsl|en|Der Standard||Der Standard}} |archive-date=2019-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145753/https://derstandard.at/2000066611637/Merkel-wuetend-ueber-Bericht-zu-May-und-Juncker |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Boffey |first=Daniel |date=2017-10-24 |title=Juncker rejects claim May begged for help at dinner meeting |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/oct/22/mays-ex-policy-chief-claims-juncker-aide-leaked-brexit-dinner-details |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=2017-10-25 |archive-date=2020-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130164611/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/oct/22/mays-ex-policy-chief-claims-juncker-aide-leaked-brexit-dinner-details |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

戴德偉翌日強調，歐盟不合作的話就不會達成有關過渡期的協議，而脫歐將如期發生。有保守黨議員擔心此舉將令英國陷入未知的未來<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/david-davis-no-deal-brexit-uk-transition-period-conservative-theresa-may-eu-relationship-a8005196.html |title=David Davis just significantly cut the odds on a 'no deal' Brexit |date=2017-10-17 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114172441/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/david-davis-no-deal-brexit-uk-transition-period-conservative-theresa-may-eu-relationship-a8005196.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

歐盟二十七個成員國領袖在19號至20號期間出席布魯塞爾的{{tsl|en|List of European Council meetings|歐洲理事會會議列表|歐洲理事會會議}}，決定是否與英國展開貿易談判<ref name="auto5">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41089257|title=Brexit: Jean-Claude Juncker criticises UK's position papers|date=2017-08-30|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]|access-date=2017-08-30|archive-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729013925/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-41089257|dead-url=no}}</ref>。歐盟成員國德國在[[2017年德国联邦议院选举|九月大選]]後一直處於看守政府狀態，戴德偉承認德國新政府可能未及完成籌組，令歐洲理事會要待十二月才可作出決議<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/07/brexit-trade-talks-deadline-slip-december-says-european-parliament/|title=Brexit trade talks deadline to slip to December, says European Parliament chief|last=Foster|first=Peter|date=2017-09-07|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2017-09-07|archive-date=2019-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708142604/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/09/07/brexit-trade-talks-deadline-slip-december-says-european-parliament/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.consilium.europa.eu/media/23512/20-euco-conclusions-art50.pdf|title=Council Conclusions|date=2017-10-20|access-date=2017-12-08|archive-date=2019-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190902193546/https://www.consilium.europa.eu/media/23512/20-euco-conclusions-art50.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。會議首日，文翠珊向約三百萬名居英歐盟僑民承諾，會讓他們以最容易方法在脫歐後留在英國<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/agreement-on-eu-citizens-in-uk-within-touching-distance-1-4590816 |title=Agreement on EU citizens in UK 'within touching distance' |date=2017-10-19 |newspaper=The Scotsman |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810220529/https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/agreement-on-eu-citizens-in-uk-within-touching-distance-1-4590816 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。翌日，圖斯克形容傳媒「誇大」脫歐談判的僵局<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41684111 |title=Brexit deadlock talk 'exaggerated' – Tusk |date=2017-10-20 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031304/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41684111 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

10月23日，文翠珊向下議院表示，她與理事會會面後，脫歐談判有「重大進展」，英國與歐盟的貿易協議只是「一步之遙」<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41720244 |title=May hails 'important progress' in EU talks |date=2017-10-23 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112022956/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-41720244 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/politics/654521/brexit-theresa-may-UK-in-touching-distance-of-brussels-deal-jeremy-corbyn-expats |title=Brits on the brink of Brexit: Theresa May says UK 'in touching distance' of Brussels deal |date=2017-10-23 |newspaper=[[每日星报|Daily Star]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145755/https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/politics/654521/brexit-theresa-may-UK-in-touching-distance-of-brussels-deal-jeremy-corbyn-expats |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但亦強調貿易協議與過渡期是唇亡齒寒<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/live/2017/oct/23/theresa-may-commons-brexit-statement-leak-saying-may-was-begging-for-help-at-dinner-with-juncker-triggers-fresh-row-with-brussels-politics-live |title=May implies UK will not implement Brexit transition unless trade deal agreed too – Politics live |first=Andrew |last=Sparrow |date=2017-10-23 |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111220924/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/live/2017/oct/23/theresa-may-commons-brexit-statement-leak-saying-may-was-begging-for-help-at-dinner-with-juncker-triggers-fresh-row-with-brussels-politics-live |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同日，容克否認德國媒體有關文翠珊在最近晚宴上「乞求幫忙」的報導<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/oct/22/mays-ex-policy-chief-claims-juncker-aide-leaked-brexit-dinner-details |title=Juncker rejects claim May begged for help at dinner meeting |first=Daniel |last=Boffey |date=2017-10-23 |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130164611/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/oct/22/mays-ex-policy-chief-claims-juncker-aide-leaked-brexit-dinner-details |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 2017年11月 ===
11月9日至10日，雙方在布魯塞爾再就脫歐舉行會談<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/programme-for-uk-eu-article-50-negotiations-9-10-november |title=Programme for UK-EU Article 50 negotiations, 9–10 November |date=2017-11-09 |website=UK Government |access-date=2017-11-10 |archive-date=2019-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810175639/https://www.gov.uk/government/news/programme-for-uk-eu-article-50-negotiations-9-10-november |dead-url=no }}</ref>。巴尼耶在閉幕記者會上確定倫敦政府需要在未來兩個星期澄清財政問題<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/nov/10/uk-given-two-week-deadline-to-make-concessions-on-brexit-divorce-bill |title=EU gives UK two-week deadline on Brexit divorce bill |last1=Boffey |first1=Daniel |date=2017-11-10 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=2017-11-10 |last2=Rankin |first2=Jennifer |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109025704/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/nov/10/uk-given-two-week-deadline-to-make-concessions-on-brexit-divorce-bill |dead-url=no }}</ref>，若非的話則下一階段談判不會如期在十二月開展<ref>{{cite web |title=Speech by Michel Barnier following the sixth round of Article 50 negotiations with the United Kingdom |url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_SPEECH-17-4545_en.htm |website=European Commission |accessdate=2017-11-11 |date=2017-11-10 |archive-date=2019-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190810175728/https://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_SPEECH-17-4545_en.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。歐盟外交官以「[[先有鸡还是先有蛋|雞先定蛋先]]」形容當前兩難僵持局面，因為只有當英國在今個月內就財政問題達成進展，歐盟才會著手處理過渡期指引<ref name=":3">{{cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/51b59608-c4a2-11e7-b2bb-322b2cb39656 |title=EU gives UK up to 3 weeks to make Brexit bill offer |last=Barker |first=Alex |last2=Parker |first2=George |date=2017-11-09 |newspaper=Financial Times |access-date=2017-11-10 |archive-date=2020-10-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024124154/https://www.ft.com/content/51b59608-c4a2-11e7-b2bb-322b2cb39656 |dead-url=no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。不過圖斯克在17號與文太在[[瑞典|瑞典]][[哥德堡|哥德堡]]會面後，表示談判沒有阻滯，且對談判能在十二月步入下一階段感到樂觀<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-tusk-may/eus-tusk-no-deadlock-on-brexit-very-cautious-but-optimistic-idUSKBN1DH20I |title=EU's Tusk: no deadlock on Brexit, very cautious but optimistic |date=2017-11-17 |agency=Reuters |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405132545/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-tusk-may/eus-tusk-no-deadlock-on-brexit-very-cautious-but-optimistic-idUSKBN1DH20I |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

11月下旬，英方的傲利·樂彬與歐方的{{tsl|en|Sabine Weyand|薩炳·偉恩}}討論財政糾紛<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/28/exclusive-britain-eu-agree-brexit-divorce-bill/ |title=Exclusive: Britain and the EU agree Brexit divorce bill |last=Foster |first=Peter |date=2017-11-28 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=2017-12-02 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-date=2020-12-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201224091103/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/28/exclusive-britain-eu-agree-brexit-divorce-bill/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另外，戴德偉拒絕歐盟提出讓北愛爾蘭留在歐盟關稅聯盟的建議，即在聯合王國內的[[愛爾蘭海|愛爾蘭海]]設下一無形海關邊界<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-politics-44764521|title=David Davis 'disagreed with UK's NI Brexit policy'|last=Campbell|first=John|date=2018-07-09|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]|accessdate=2020-12-15|archive-date=2019-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726183606/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-politics-44764521|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 2017年12月 ===
12月4日，文翠珊與容克在布魯塞爾舉行會面，完善脫歐協議草稿，其中財政問題和公民權利有進展，但兩愛問題則令協議宣告失敗。雖然愛爾蘭總理瓦拉德卡表態支持建議，但未能獲得北愛爾蘭的[[民主统一党_(北爱尔兰)|民主統一黨]]的支持<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/983b64e8-d8e0-11e7-a039-c64b1c09b482 |title=Brexit deal falls through over Irish border dispute |last1=Barker |first1=Alex |last2=Beesley |first2=Arthur |date=2017-12-04 |newspaper=Financial Times |access-date=2017-12-06 |last3=Parker |first3=George |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109035146/https://www.ft.com/content/983b64e8-d8e0-11e7-a039-c64b1c09b482 |dead-url=no }}{{subscription}}</ref>。會議在之後數日繼續，雙方談判代表在8號皆同意「一同意就要同意全部」原則，並發表聯合報告，回顧脫歐協議中的承諾。雙方在三項議題上達成「原則上協定」<ref name=":4">{{cite web |url=https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/joint_report.pdf |title=Joint report from the negotiators of the European Union and the United Kingdom Government on progress during phase 1 of negotiations under Article 50 TEU on the United Kingdom's orderly withdrawal from the European Union |date=2017-12-08 |website=European Commission |access-date=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2019-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009055825/https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/joint_report.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>：
* 保護英國國內歐盟公民和歐盟境內英國公民的權利（就此共識的詳情則另列在技術性聯合說明<ref>{{cite web|title=Joint technical note expressing the detailed consensus of the UK and EU positions on Citizens' Rights|url=https://ec.europa.eu/commission/publications/joint-technical-note-expressing-detailed-consensus-uk-and-eu-positions-respect-citizens-rights_en|date=2017-12-08|website=European Commission|access-date=2017-12-15|archive-date=2020-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001055231/https://ec.europa.eu/commission/publications/joint-technical-note-expressing-detailed-consensus-uk-and-eu-positions-respect-citizens-rights_en|dead-url=no}}</ref>）；
* 應對北愛爾蘭獨特情形的框架；
* 解決財政爭拗。
至於延遲至下一談判階段才討論的議題包括<ref name=":4" />：
* 脫歐時居住在歐盟的英國僑民搬居另一歐盟國家的權利，以及該些英僑返回英國的權利；
* 脫歐時已相互認證以外的專業資歷認證。
容克稱協議是脫歐談判一大突破<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-42277040 |title='Breakthrough' deal in Brexit talks |date=2017-12-08 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]] |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-12-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218135243/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-42277040 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，並正式宣佈開展涉及脫歐後英歐貿易的第二階段談判<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/britain-and-eu-reach-divorce-deal-to-move-on-to-new-phase-in-brexit-talks/2017/12/08/4525b332-dba4-11e7-a241-0848315642d0_story.html |title=Britain and E.U. reach divorce deal to move on to new phase in Brexit talks |first=Michael |last=Birnbaum |date=2017-12-08 |newspaper=The Washington Post |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2020-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922162544/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/britain-and-eu-reach-divorce-deal-to-move-on-to-new-phase-in-brexit-talks/2017/12/08/4525b332-dba4-11e7-a241-0848315642d0_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu/may-travels-to-brussels-in-hope-of-clinching-brexit-deal-idUSKBN1E20G6 |title=Britain, EU clinch Brexit 'breakthrough' with move to trade talks |date=2017-12-09 |agency=Reuters |accessdate=2017-12-09 |archive-date=2019-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322145748/https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu/may-travels-to-brussels-in-hope-of-clinching-brexit-deal-idUSKBN1E20G6 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。談判將涵蓋過渡期安排和未來雙邊關係（尤其貿易和安全）的框架<ref>{{cite web|title=Brexit deal: Theresa May's agreement with Brussels|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-42280487|date=2017-12-08|last=Morris|first=Chris|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]|access-date=2017-12-11|archive-date=2020-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130204809/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-42280487|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=The Irish Times|date=2017-12-08|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/uk/brexit-breakthrough-may-pledges-no-hard-border-as-commission-says-sufficient-progress-made-1.3320030|accessdate=2017-12-08|title=Brexit breakthrough: May pledges 'no hard border' as commission says 'sufficient progress' made}}</ref>。

12月7日，[[馬丁·舒爾茨|馬丁·舒爾茨]]的[[德国社会民主党|社會民主黨]]同意與默克爾的基民盟磋商籌組聯合政府，但前提是在2025年前組建「[[歐羅巴合眾國|歐羅巴合眾國]]」，將不願組國的歐盟成員國驅逐離開<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/dec/07/martin-schulz-united-states-of-europe-germany-sdp |title=Martin Schulz wants 'United States of Europe' within eight years |first=Philip |last=Oltermann |date=2017-12-07 |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=2017-12-08 |archive-date=2021-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118003505/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/dec/07/martin-schulz-united-states-of-europe-germany-sdp |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

12月15號，歐洲理事會同意採用第二階段談判的指引，談判將於2018年初開啟。決議又確定第一階段談判充足，而雙方的承諾亦應「鄭重且盡快轉變為法律詞彙」，並指出英國提出的過渡期為期「約兩年」，並於2018年初開始<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2017/12/15/european-council-art-50-guidelines-for-brexit-negotiations/|title=European Council (Art. 50) guidelines for Brexit negotiations|date=2017-12-15|website=European Council|access-date=2017-12-15|archive-date=2020-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201104020134/https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/press/press-releases/2017/12/15/european-council-art-50-guidelines-for-brexit-negotiations/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-42368096|title=Brexit: EU leaders agree to move talks to next stage|date=2017-12-15|access-date=2017-12-19|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|英國廣播公司新聞]]|archive-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729030025/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-42368096|dead-url=no}}</ref>。20號，歐盟委員會草擬談判命令，確立過渡期不應在2020年12月31日後延續。過渡期間的英國將不會是歐盟與他國的協議成員國，例如《[[加拿大-歐盟綜合經濟與貿易協定|綜合經濟與貿易協定]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/annex_commissions_recommendation_20-12-2017.pdf|title=Commission's recommendation including supplementary negotiating directives|date=2017-12-20|website=European Commission|access-date=2017-12-21|archive-date=2020-12-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201227051412/https://ec.europa.eu/commission/sites/beta-political/files/annex_commissions_recommendation_20-12-2017.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

